Security Considerations for Dark Mode Toggle
============================================

1. Input validation: localStorage theme value is validated against a strict
   allow-list ['light', 'dark']. Tampered values are discarded and cleared.
2. Storage safety: All localStorage access is wrapped in try/catch to handle
   sandboxed iframes, private browsing, and quota errors.
3. DOM safety: We only toggle a CSS class on <html>. No user-controlled string
   is injected into innerHTML/DOM, eliminating XSS surface.
4. Rate limiting: Toggle button enforces a 150ms minimum interval between
   activations to prevent event-flood abuse.
5. Accessibility as security: aria-pressed, aria-label, and focus-visible
   ring ensure the control is usable by assistive tech and keyboard — reducing
   the risk of users being unable to exit a state.
6. Privacy / GDPR: Theme preference is a non-identifying functional setting,
   not PII. No consent banner required under GDPR Recital 30 (strictly
   necessary functional cookies/storage). No retention policy needed — user
   can clear via browser storage controls.
7. No network calls; entirely client-side. No new third-party deps introduced,
   so no new supply-chain surface.
